    <p>Cheong Soo Pieng: Am­bi­tion For Orig­i­nal­ity</p>
    <p>This ex­hi­bi­tion fea­tures 10 sig­nif­i­cant works by late Sin­ga­pore artist</p>
    <p>Cheong Soo Pieng which are highly stylised in vi­su­als and themes. Cheong was a pi­o­neer of the</p>
    <p>Nanyang art style and a key fig­ure in Sin­ga­pore’s mod­ern art scene.</p>
    <p>Over a five-decade ca­reer, he es­tab­lished a unique and wide-rang­ing reper­toire of styles and medi­ums.</p>
    <p>art­com­mune gallery,</p>
    <p>01-01 Carl­ton Ho­tel, 76 Bras Basah Road City Hall Aug 1 - 16, noon - 7pm daily Free</p>
    <p>www.art­com­mune.com.sg</p>
    <p>Mythol­ogy: The Remix</p>
    <p>In this on­line ex­hi­bi­tion by the Sin­ga­pore Chi­nese Cul­tural Cen­tre, 20 young artists give a mod­ern twist to Chi­nese mythol­ogy and rein­ter­pret Chi­nese char­ac­ters through street-style art.</p>
    <p>View it at bit.ly/39kexQz On­go­ing Free</p>


